---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const board = [
  { name: 'Adam', email: 'adam@dc402.org' },
  { name: 'Bryan', email: 'bryan@dc402.org' },
  { name: 'Henry', email: 'henry@dc402.org' },
  { name: 'Jason', email: 'jason@dc402.org' },
  { name: 'Tim', email: 'tim@dc402.org' },
];

const founders = [
  { name: 'Jessi' },
  { name: 'Brad' },
];
---
<Base title="About Us">
  <h2 class="page-heading">About Us</h2>

  <div class="card about-card">
    <p>DC402 is Omaha's DEF CON Group, gathering every <strong>second Tuesday</strong> of the month at a central Omaha venue.
    We are an informal, social community that leans technical but stays genuinely welcoming to anyone curious about security and technology.</p>

    <p>Our members span a wide range of backgrounds: U.S. government and military, digital forensics, law enforcement, capture-the-flag competitors, industry practitioners, academics, and people who simply want to understand how things work.
    That breadth is intentional. Good ideas come from diverse perspectives, and we would rather have a big tent than a narrow one.</p>

    <p>Talks at our meetings are most often security-related, but we welcome drifts into adjacent territory including tech policy, privacy, hardware, radio, and anything technically interesting.
    You do not need to be an expert to present. A curious question, a weekend project, or a half-finished idea is more than enough to get on the schedule.</p>

    <p>DC402 is a registered <strong>501(c)(3)</strong> non-profit organization.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section-heading">Active Board</div>
  <div class="people-grid">
    {board.map(m => (
      <div class="person-card card">
        <div class="person-name">{m.name}</div>
        <a href={`mailto:${m.email}`} class="person-email">{m.email}</a>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>

  <div class="section-heading alumni-heading">Alumni</div>
  <p class="alumni-note">Jessi and Brad helped put in the early work that got DC402 off the ground. They have since moved on to new cities, but their contributions are appreciated.</p>
  <div class="people-grid alumni-grid">
    {founders.map(f => (
      <div class="person-card card alumni-card">
        <div class="person-name">{f.name}</div>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .about-card p { font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 1.1rem; }
  .about-card p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .about-card strong { color: var(--text); }

  .section-heading {
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .alumni-heading { color: var(--text-muted); }

  .alumni-note {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .people-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(160px, 1fr));
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .person-card {
    padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.3rem;
  }

  .person-name { font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text); }
  .person-email { font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; transition: color 0.15s; }
  .person-email:hover { color: var(--accent-light); }
  .person-email.muted { color: var(--text-muted); pointer-events: none; }

  .alumni-card { opacity: 0.6; }
</style>
